==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ostent
<hw>Os"tent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ostentus</ets>, <ets>ostentum</ets>, fr. <ets>ostendere</ets> (p.
p. <ets>ostensus</ets> and <ets>ostentus</ets>) to show. See
<er>Ostensible</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Appearance; air; mien.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Manifestation; token; portent.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We asked of God that some <qex>ostent</qex> might clear⟦br⟧
Our cloudy business, who gave us sign.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ostentate</ent>⟦br⟧
